<!-- Purpose: To test select element with the multiple attribute -->

<!-- Expected result: Should create a drop-down menu with three selections; you should be able to select more than one of them (as with a checkbox) -->

<title>XHTML Functional -- SELECT - MULTIPLE</title>

</head>

<body>

<p>The select element below allows the option of selecting multiple menu items.</p>

<p>Place focus in the field and drag cursor to highlight multiple items.</p>

<form action=""><select multiple="multiple" size="5">

<option>Assam</option>

<option>Darjeeling</option>

<option>Keemun</option>

<option>Sencha</option>

<option>Yunnan</option>

</select></form>

</body>

